section.section:
The regulations shall include provisions relating to:
the manner and deadline for a gubernatorial ticket to notify the State Board of its intention to qualify for a public contribution;
the deadline for a gubernatorial ticket to submit a request for a public contribution;
the dates when the State Board will authorize, and the Comptroller will make, distributions of public contributions to gubernatorial tickets in accordance with this title;
a proportionate distribution when there is not, or may not be, sufficient money in the Fund;
a formula for distributing a supplementary public contribution to the other eligible gubernatorial tickets if additional money becomes available because:
an eligible gubernatorial ticket fails to request a public contribution;
an eligible gubernatorial ticket withdraws as a gubernatorial ticket; or
an eligible gubernatorial ticket is disqualified;
the standards by which expenditures by campaign finance entities with which an eligible gubernatorial ticket is affiliated are applied to the expenditure limit prescribed in § 15-105 of this title;
thresholds for in-kind contributions that are not considered contributions or expenditures for the purposes of this title;
distributions to:
an unopposed gubernatorial ticket;
a gubernatorial ticket composed of members from other than the two principal political parties; and
a write-in gubernatorial ticket; and
the purposes for which a public contribution may not be used.
